The paper presents a heuristic algorithm for improving the results of k-means optimization, which is a common machine learning technique used in various fields such as computer vision, natural language processing, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also mentions the use of k-means in clustering text data, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of k-means in image segmentation, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
